To date, 605,991 COVID-19 tests have been conducted. JOHANNESBURG - Forty-three more people have died from the coronavirus in the country, taking the death toll to 524. The health department has announced 649 new cases on Tuesday night. The total number of positive cases now stands at 24,264. READ: COVID-19 a 'setback' for Africa, says Pandor Almost 606,000 tests have been conducted to date. Recoveries stand at 12,741. The Western Cape still has the highest number of positive cases with 15,829 cases followed by Gauteng with 3,043 cases and the Eastern Cape with 2,864 cases. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.